                    </div>
                    <span>If you are a collector of early photos,and you also collect books on early photo collections,this book is a must as an extremely important part of your collection.It contains several pages of readable text on some noted lynching events in small but sufficient enough detail,descriptions of plates and their photo types in the back,and what other early historical photo collection book are you going such a wealth of this type of portrait?I rate this one up there with Stanley Burn's sleeping beauty(another important photo collector book).There is no doubt that this book is a must!Just get it!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">What Man can do to Man</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
